  "texts": [
    "They wrote prompts corresponding to existing legal reasoning techniques for a task that requires the lawyer to determine whether a hypothesis is true or false based on a given premise.",
    "Finally, Choi et al. (2023) asked ChatGPT to complete various law school exams involving both essay and multiple choice questions; it earned a C+ score.",
    "Similarly to our research, Nay et al. (2023) and Blair-Stanek et al. (2023) gave versions of the text-davinci-003 model legal reasoning tasks outside of an examination setting, asking it to apply statutes to answer questions and evaluating its performance systematically.",
    "Nay et al. (2023) used multiple choice questions for this task.",
    "Blair-Stanek et al. (2023) used the StAtutory Reasoning Assessment (SARA) data set for their task, finding that GPT-3 performed significantly better than BERT, foot_2 but \"performed at chance (0.5) or worse in the zero-shot tests where there was no statute included.\""
  ],
